  "text": "The suppression of bAP evoked [Ca 2+ ] i increases we observed could be evoked by several mechanisms. The greatest suppression was induced by the large [Ca 2+ ] i increases generated by Ca 2+ waves and NMDA spikes. While these events have not been detected in vivo under physiological conditions (possibly because the appropriate experiments have not been performed) they both can be induced in slices with moderate intensity (subthreshold for AP generation) tetanic synaptic stimulation -a protocol which is widely used in synaptic plasticity experiments. In addition, a clear but smaller suppression could be achieved with trains of bAPs, which are similar to bursts sometimes recorded in vivo [CITATION_1] .",
